{
  "texts": [
    "Second, AI can also be applied to simulate the interaction between odorant molecules and receptor proteins.",
    "For example, deep learning models trained on molecular structure data can predict receptor binding affinities.",
    "These approaches capture the many-to-many relationships underlying combinatorial coding and help map odorant-receptor interaction networks.",
    "In this way, AI supports the interpretation of complex neural and molecular signals, contributing to a more comprehensive understanding of olfactory perception.",
    "These models not only improve biological realism but also assist in tasks such as odor prediction, classification, and novel scent discovery."
  ]
}